description: Archeologist Howard Carter is on hard times, being kicked out of the business while there are tantalizing rumors about the tomb of someone named Tutankhamun and a pharaoh buried in the Valley of Kings... meanwhile, we witness Tut's boyhood and deepening relationship with his sister, Ankhe...

Lex and Tim Murphy, the well-to-do grandchildren of dearly departed John Hammond, are all grown up and carrying on Hammond's legacy. While Lex is quelling a public outcry to re-open Jurassic Park, Tim is secretly helping create a new batch of kinder, gentler dinosaurs that are currently hatching in a secret location... until one leaves the nest and begins tearing up a small Texas town!
name: Redemption Chapter Two

description: The unquenchable rage of Thor knows no satisfaction! It is an earlier day. The perverse and unjust TRIAL OF THOR has left the God of Thunder resentful and bitter. Fed up with Asgard, he has quit the gods and taken up with the world of men...joined a humble community...taken a wife. But when the bloody tides of Asgard's battles lap even at the shores of Earth, Thor must take up arms once more -- or risk everything he now loves being eradicated under an unstoppable tide of death and destruction...

Including the twist no one saw coming, the most hellish date ever conceived, and the return of everybody's favorite nightmare, Spanish Scott! The Collected Stray Bullets Series is a perfect introduction for new readers, a great way for fans to complete the series, and it looks like a million and six bucks on the shelf next to the first five volumes!

description:
In 1796, while Napoleon Bonaparte's troops ride roughshod over France's foes, Dracula gains vampiric sway over a selfish young woman named Mirka, the daughter of Count Bogdan, in order to increase his earthly power by marriage.

Realizing belatedly that Dracula is one of the undead, Bogdan leads a handful of soldiers into his castle, intending to slay the vampire. But Bogdan's men are instead slain by Dracula and Dracula has Bogdan's newly-undead daughter slay her father.

Meanwhile, having come from the Arctic into the Transylvanian Alps in search of a way to make himself a mate, the Monster created by Victor Frankenstein has been befreinded by a girl named Irena. When French troops ransack her village, Irena convinces him to defend it against the brutish soldier called "Monsieur Massacre". But the Mosnter must give way when their leader, the magician Count St. Germain, holds the girl hostage.

St. Germain, who claims to have been kept alive for centuries by a mystic elixir, has come to obtain the one ingredient he still needs in order for the liquid to grant eternal life: the undead heart of a vampire.

Concerned for Irena, the Monster swiftly travels by foot to the wild Carpathian mountains...and into Castle Dracula.

Issue 1 of 3 published by Topps Comics
name: Part 1: The Gathering Storm

description:
Beth and Virginia have relocated to Los Angeles where things only appear more normal... Take a ringside seat for these brutal tales of twisted emotion that will knock you to the mat and have you seeing stars...

Collects STRAY BULLETS #15-22.

Other People collects the entire third story arc of David Lapham's critically acclaimed series. Stray Bullets issues #15-22 the way they were meant to be seen! This larger-than-life hardcover features never-before-seen scripts, character sketches, and other behind-the-scenes extras. Volume 3 weaves together the sick and depraved lives of ordinary Americans. Watch as they follow down the path of sin, crime, and emotional vampirism! With startling realism, these new characters slowly weave their way into the lost lives of an old familiar cast like Virginia Applejack, Beth, Monster, and Amy Racecar. Eisner Award-winner for its beautiful style and design, this hardcover is a perfect introduction for new readers and an absolute must for every true Stray Bullets fan.

Oversized Hardcover or normal sized soft cover, collects #15-22 of Stray Bullets
name: Volume Three

description: Daredevil, the blind avenger of Hell’s Kitchen faces a life changing decision when he is presented with the chance to see again. But at what cost will Matt regain his sight? Guest starring Bullseye! The Kingpin of crime, ever the Machiavellian mastermind, uses lawyer Matt Murdock’s quest for justice against him in a deadly money-making scheme. And the Man Without Fear finds himself embroiled in a gang war in Japan. All this and much more in this all-new, all-black-and-white one-shot in the spirit of the Mighty Marvel Magazines of yore, but ALL-NOW in style!
name: Second Sight; Secrets and Lies; Game Room

description:
By holding hostage a young woman named Irena, the magician known as Count Saint-Germain forces the Monster created by Victor Frankenstein to invade Castle Dracula. The sorcerer, who claims to be centuries old, desires the undead heart of the vampire to generate an elixir granting eternal life.

The Monster does violent battle with Count Dracula, but neither of these two strange life forms can slay the other.

Their supernatural combat is interrupted when St. Germain and French soldiers attack the vampire. After killing the troops, Dracula is at the mercy of St. Germain- when the Monster intervenes and kills the magician. The perhaps- immortal Monster has decided he has more in common with the ageless vampire than with mortal men.

Dracula pretends to befriend the Monster, whose journeys across Europe arouse in him a desire to see the far parts of the world one day. The Monster and Irena, for whom he feels a great tenderness, linger for a time at Castle Dracula.

One night, Mirka, Dracula's undead paramour, tries to seduce (or perhaps merely to drink the blood of) the Monster. When he spurns her, she taunts Dracula into killing Irena while she walks alone in the nearby forest.

When the monster encounters the now-vampiric Irena, he is forced to slay her to free her soul.

Realizing this is Dracula's handiwork, the Monster vows to make war on the Lord of Vampires...

This is the second issue of a three part series.
name: Part 2: The Grand Alliance

description:
Enraged by the death of his beloved Irena at the hands of Count Dracula, the Monster created by Victor Frankenstein declares war!

His first act is to go to Castle Dracula and find Dracula's undead bride Mirka whom he had spurned only nights before. They battle ferociously, Mirka revealing that she had tempted Dracula to kill Irena. In his fury, the Monster utterly destroys Mirka tossing her decapitated head at Dracula's feet in vengeance.

The Lord of Vampires and the Monster of Frankenstein engage in a titanic struggle which levels Castle Dracula but neither can get the upper hand. Realizing this, the Monster simply walks away...
name: Triumph and Tragedy

description: Filled with destiny, purpose, and seven million years of DECEPTICON-whuppin’ to catch up on, IRONHIDE goes out to meet the Swarm in an epic final confrontation. Casey Coller and Mike Costa  deliver what is far and away the most action-packed issue of their careers, and the fate of CYBERTRON is changed forever.
name: Any Old Iron

description: When Nami, the granddaughter of a rival swordsmith, tries to use her girlish charms to squeeze information from Goemon about his mighty sword, Ryusei... Lupin and Goemon pull the old switcheroo on Gramps for the last laugh. Then, when a college filmmaker's "mockumentary" about the death of Inspector Zenigata lures Lupin into a trap, it turns out Fujiko has put out a little misinformation of her own. The results could serve as a crash course on how NOT to make a movie.
name: Vol. 6

description: Lupin, the World's Most Wanted, is taking burglary to a whole new level with plans to commit five jobs simultaneously! While searching for a dead criminal's treasure, Lupin also encounters a crazy witch hired by the Nezumi Clan. Will he find a way to outwit the nitwit witch?
name: Vol. 7

description: The lascivious adventures continue as Lupin tests Zenigata's resolve with an assortment of brilliant disguises and seductive schemes. Later, a gold figurine becomes the object of everyone's desire, and Lupin's plan to steal back the cherished treasure might send him through the roof. But this action-packed volume chronicling the original international man of mystery definitely proves one thing: When you have sexy girls in steaming hot springs, you better hold onto to your gun!
name: Vol. 8

description: Practice makes perfect for Lupin and the crew as they rehearse for their latest heist...but will they crumble under the pressure of the spotlight?! And later, during a daring mission at the museum, Inspector Zenigata may have finally come up with a way to confound our Master Thief! Think that'll stop Lupin? Of course not!
name: Vol. 9

description:
Julin Kenga had always thought that she was an only child and heiress to her martial arts clan. So, it comes as quite a surprise when an old kung-fu master gives her a magical bell and tells her to find her two older sisters. She must find them quickly because the evil King Baiwon is trying to capture the three bells that the Kenga sisters hold. Finding her first sister is not so hard - Juline finds Kaline in a nearby town...but the third - and oldest - sister is another matter entirely...Seiline, a pirate captain(!), will not believe that the other two are her sisters unless they defeat her in combat...

Chapter List

  • Chapter 1: The Wrath of Julin
  • Chapter 2: The Journey Begins
  • Chapter 3: The Secret of the Bells
  • Chapter 4: The Pirate Queen
  • Chapter 5: Big Sister
name: Vol. 1

description:
Julin and Kalin have finally been united with their older sister, Seilin. But it's no family picnic. The hardened Seilin wants a fight before she gives her younger siblings any clues to their father's past. But the family feud is interrupted by the devious Bai Wang, leader of the White Lotus Clan. She wants the mysterious bells that the sisters possess, claiming they can unleash a terrible power that has been long forgotten. It's all-out action in this exciting volume of Shaolin Sisters.

Chapter List

  • Chapter 6: Fighting Lessons
  • Chapter 7: Abandoned
  • Chapter 8: The White Queen
  • Chapter 9: The Fierce Battle
  • Chapter 10: The Stolen Bell
name: Vol. 2

description:
The Shaolin Sisters--Julin, Kalin and Seilin--are in search of their stolen bells. The hunt is urgent, as the nefarious Bai Wang intends to use the magical bells to unleash a horrible power. Bai Wang's formidable fortress now looms large before the sisters. But as the stalwart siblings ready their raid, the mysterious masked man known as Drake swoops in on the action and fiercely battles Bai Wang for control of the bells. In the skirmish, Drake is unmasked--and the revelation of his true identity is enough to shatter Julin's stone fist!

Chapter List

  • Chapter 11: The Killer's Conscience
  • Chapter 12: Drake's Return!
  • Chapter 13: Reunion
  • Chapter 14: Grand Melee
  • Chapter 15: Stone Fist Rising
name: Vol. 3

description: Months after a devastating plague ends World War I, Europe is suddenly flooded with deadly vampires. Lord Henry Baltimore, a soldier determined to wipe out the monsters, is on the hunt for the creature responsible for this chaos and his own personal tragedy. What he uncovers is a terror as horrific and frightening as any he's seen on the battlefield.
name: Part One (of Five)

description: Tom Strong has traveled back to 1939 and he's racing to prevent his evil son from recruiting an army that will allow the Nazis to conquer the world - the unstoppable Robots of Doom! Accompanied by his younger self, Tom faces a fatal showdown in the caverns of the Dero robots and is forced to seek aid from one of his deadliest enemies!
name: Part Three: Caving In

volume.name: Tom Strong and the Robots of Doom

description: The nightmare visions are coming true as Magog's fate becomes more and more entwined with the Psy-Cho Twins. It's all coming to a head, too, as their hand is forced to ensure that "Kingdom Come" doesn't become a reality!
name: Blown To Kingdom Come, Chapter Two
